args: Thank you for breakfast, Cleo.\nIt was divine as always.

Actually, I was hoping to talk to you for
a moment. It may not be my business,
but are you certain it's all right to leave
Quinbell unattended for so long?
Yeah, ain't you the mayor?\nOr, like, the substitute mayor?
No need to worry! I passed out a perfect\nset of instructional documents to keep\nthings running smoothly without me.
Also, as the acting mayor, it is important\nto broaden one's horizons.
That is why I decided to stay with you for\na while and gain a bit of life experience!\nA fine plan, don't you think?
That nose goes any higher in the air,\nshe's gonna be snortin' clouds.
You're welcome to stay as long as you\nlike, but won't your friends miss you?
Yes, you seemed quite close to...\nSandy and Becky, was it?
Oh, I think they'll get along just fine\nwithout me. Honestly, it's high time I\ngot smarter about choosing my friends.

Cluck your tongues and wag your fingers
all you like, but it's mere fact that people
understand best those of their same
social standing.
Man, her ice just became a BURN!
It is well known that those of similar\nbirth and upbringing tend to understand\neach other best.
Look, I ain't gonna pretend I don't\nget confused by human cultural\nstuff sometimes...
But learning about new things like\nthat is the fun part!
It's not always fun. There are times when\none's standing gets in the way of making a\ntrue connection.
Though you deliver your point most\nforcefully, it is not wholly wrong.
You see? In order for people to truly\nunderstand each other, they must\nspeak with one of equal status.
So who of us would count as being\n＂of your status,＂ Catherine?
Why, a proper young lady, of course!

Someone with a good family and
upbringing... Highly educated...
An impeccable social etiquette...
Yes, that is a good place to start.
Oh, I think I got JUST\nthe lady for you...
I hope you do not mind me joining you\non this mission, Lady Julietta?
I'm bettin' Julietta and her are gonna\nget along like two peas in a...whatever\nit is that peas come in.
Status should not be an issue, at least...
It's Catherine, yes? Well, I'd be happy to\nhave you join us, but as you are not a\nfighter, this mission might be a bit dan—
No need to trouble yourself over me!\nI have perfect mastery over the basic\nfighting techniques.

Plus, this is a wonderful chance for me to
gain some life experience and be prepared
the next time a pack of fiends deigns to
invade my bucolic home.
At home, my family attendants are always\nguarding me, so I don't get opportunities\nlike this for proper training.
All right. I expect it will be fine with\nJulietta and myself along.
Thank you. Then I shall return to my room\nto prepare.
I wonder what prompted her to talk of\nchoosing friends...
Incredible, Catherine! Honestly, I'm rather\nsurprised at how well you've taken to this.
I could not allow myself to remain a\nhelpless child protected by servants.\n
I seek to keep safe my home of Quinbell,\nas well as the people I hold dear.
You won't get off so easily if you make\nBecky cry again!
As the perfect woman, I will not forgive\nany act that harms my friends!
Anyone of note would have done\nthe same for a friend, my dear.
Where is your father today, Catherine?
He left on a business trip to the capital.
Ah, my parents are out of town, too.
For one of their academic conferences?\nIs it another long one?
With the travel time on top, I don't expect\nto see them again for a month.
Still, as long as I have you and Becky,\nI know I won't be lonely!
What happened to the amazing fighter\nwe saw but a moment before?
My apologies: I fear my concentration\nescaped me for a moment.
To let slip your guard for even a moment\nin battle is to gamble your own life.\nDo not let this happen again.
Understood. I shall be more diligent.
(Oh, I'm nothing but a fool! I left town to\nescape my so-called friends, and yet find\nI can think on nothing else!)
(And now that concern has led me down\nthe primrose path of failure...)
(Perfect? Ha! It would be a kindness\nto name me mediocre at this point.)
(There are so many amazing people\nhere in the castle...)
(Even Lady Julietta, who seemed like she\nwas from a similar background as me...)
(Yet her education, behavior, and fighting\nskills clearly surpass my own.)
I thought myself a perfect lady\nthat could do anything...
But if I do not have that,\nwhat am I left with...?
